  <RulesElement name="Light the Way" type="Ritual" internal-id="ID_TIV_RITUAL_MAGICAL_MEMORIES_100_2" source="Magical Memories from Beyond: Forgotten Rituals" revision-date="1/11/2011 3:22:33 PM">
    <Flavor> A series of tiny metallic disks bask under the bright daylight within the splendid representation of a sun that you have drawn prior to this elementary ceremony; a part of this light will remain trapped at their cores, and with a small magical incentive be released later. </Flavor>
    <specific name="Category"> Creation </specific>
    <specific name="Key Skill"> Arcana </specific>
    <specific name="Component Cost"> 10 gp </specific>
    <specific name="Duration"> Special </specific>
    <specific name="Level"> 1 </specific>
    <specific name="Time"> 1 hour </specific>
    <specific name="Market Price"> 50 gp </specific>
    <specific name="Prerequisite" />
    <specific name="type"> Ritual </specific>
This simple ritual creates a given number of small receptacles, such as coins or crystal pieces, which sole purpose is to double the duration of a Light when this cantrip is cast upon one, although a given receptacle can receive only a limited number of such cantrips before being utterly exhausted, the number of enhanced Light being fixed at the completion of the ritual. The other advantage is that even if a second Light or more are cast, all those previously placed upon such receptacles remain active nonetheless - contrary to what happens when you normally use this cantrip - winking out only when a 10 minutes period have been reached.

The Arcana check result made during the ritual determines how many receptacles are created and the number of Light they can receive before they become inert.

&lt;table&gt;Arcana Check Result	Number of Receptacles Created	Number of Enhanced Lights Provided by One Receptacle
9 or lower	5	1d4+1
10-14	6	1d4+2
15-19	7	1d4+3
20-24	8	1d4+4
25-29	9	1d4+5
30 or higher	10	10&lt;/table&gt;

</RulesElement>
