</RulesElement>
  <RulesElement name="Marilith's Arms" type="Ritual" internal-id="ID_TIV_RITUAL_MAGICAL_MEMORIES_100_3" source="Magical Memories from Beyond: Forgotten Rituals" revision-date="1/11/2011 3:22:33 PM">
    <Flavor> You stretch out on the floor, superimposing your body with the accurate, life-sized drawing of the marilith represented there. Then you overlay your arms upon the upper limbs pertaining to the she-demon portrayal and in no time you feel an extreme pressure building up within your sides. After a brief moment the pain becomes almost unbearable as two new pairs of appendages begin to gradually emerge from your flanks.</Flavor>
    <specific name="Category"> Exploration </specific>
    <specific name="Key Skill"> Arcana or Religion </specific>
    <specific name="Component Cost"> 6,000 gp plus 4 healing surges </specific>
    <specific name="Duration"> Special </specific>
    <specific name="Level"> 20 </specific>
    <specific name="Time"> 1 hour </specific>
    <specific name="Market Price"> 24,000 gp </specific>
    <specific name="Prerequisite" />
    <specific name="type"> Ritual </specific>
Like its namesake indicates this ritual provides the recipient with a total of six arms but moreover with powers being generally the sole preserve of the she-serpentine demons. The Arcana or Religion check determines for how long the arms and the abilities last and also specifies the number of powers granted, which are chosen by the recipient among the list below; since these powers are those of a marilith see the D&amp;D 4E MONSTER MANUAL to know how they work. Of course, all the attacks delivered via these powers use the character's own abilities scores.

* Hacking Blades
* Resist 20 variable
* Shroud of Steel
* The Abyssal Lady (special). This incomparable power can be selected only by a woman coming from one of the following races: dwarf, eladrin, elf, half-elf, or human. The Abyssal Lady enables a female of the aforementioned races to turn her legs into a serpentine tail, and to use either the speed of a marilith of her own speed, whichever is best. The recipient gains darkvision and is automatically proficient with scimitars even if she wasn't before. Moreover, The Abyssal Lady is considered as a Large creature and has Reach 2 for her attacks. Note that accessing this power requires one more healing surge.
* Weapon Dance

The character reverts to her normal self either at the end of the time period or as soon as she has participated in as many encounters as stipulated in parentheses, whichever comes first.

The ritual's components include six scimitars. At least one of these curved blades must be silvered and another ought to be magical. The ritual randomly consumes as many blades as the recipient gains powers.

&lt;table&gt;Arcana or Religion Check Result	Duration	Number of Powers
19 or lower	1 hour (1 encounter)	1
20-24	2 hour (2 encounters)	2
25-29	3 hour (3 encounters)	3
30-34	4 hour (4 encounters)	4
35 or higher	5 hour (5 encounters)	All (Dependent upon sex)&lt;/table&gt;

</RulesElement>
