</RulesElement>
  <RulesElement name="Phantasmal Miner" type="Ritual" internal-id="ID_TIV_RITUAL_MAGICAL_MEMORIES_100_4" source="Magical Memories from Beyond: Forgotten Rituals" revision-date="1/11/2011 3:22:33 PM">
    <Flavor> The swirling smoke gradually takes shape, turning into a stout, ghostly fellow that briefly looks severely at you. The phantasmal humanoid then grabs the tools you have placed upon the ground prior to its arrival and sets to work at your command, excavating earth and rock at a wild pace. </Flavor>
    <specific name="Category"> Exploration </specific>
    <specific name="Key Skill"> Arcana or Religion </specific>
    <specific name="Component Cost"> 75 GP </specific>
    <specific name="Duration"> Special </specific>
    <specific name="Level"> 5 </specific>
    <specific name="Time"> 10 minutes </specific>
    <specific name="Market Price"> 250 gp </specific>
    <specific name="Prerequisite" />
    <specific name="type"> Ritual </specific>
This ritual creates a ghostly, dwarf-like humanoid, which can dig a hole, remove gravel, or tunnel a way out through earth and rock alike as required, though it does so only if you give it specific instructions and if you moreover provide the mining implements required for the job, such as a spade or a shovel. The phantasmal miner cannot fight on your behalf nor interact with other creatures, being limited to labor-intensive jobs. The Arcana or Religion check fix the duration of service of the ghostlike worker as well as the amount of matter it can remove. If a cave in, landslide, or suchlike event ever occurs while the entity works the phantom is unaffected and simply comes back to receive new instructions, though it most likely needs new tools in order to resume the task. Finally, the phantasmal miner cannot travel at more than 20 squares away from the spot where it first appeared.

&lt;table&gt;Arcana or Religion Check Result	Duration	Cubic Feet Excavated
14 or lower	1 hour	10 of loose earth, or 5 of broken rock, or 1 of sheer rock
15-19	2 hours	20 of loose earth, or 10 of broken rock, or 2 of sheer rock
20-24	3 hours	30 of loose earth, or 15 of broken rock, or 3 of sheer rock
25-29	4 hours	40 of loose earth, or 20 of broken rock, or 4 of sheer rock
30 or higher	5 hours	50 of loose earth, or 25 of broken rock, or 5 of sheer rock)&lt;/table&gt;

</RulesElement>
