  <RulesElement name="Snow-Glass" type="Ritual" internal-id="ID_TIV_RITUAL_MAGICAL_MEMORIES_100_5" source="Magical Memories from Beyond: Forgotten Rituals" revision-date="1/11/2011 3:22:33 PM">
    <Flavor> The window, which has been discreetly etched with a symbol prior to its destruction, breaks under the violent impact, miraculously without the slightest sound; the second wonder is that the thousands of shards thus produced never fall to the ground. Instead, the pieces of broken glass stay aloft, slowly taking on the shape of a whirling cloud that surrounds in the blink of an eye like a sheen the now smiling vandal and would-be thief. </Flavor>
    <specific name="Category"> Exploration </specific>
    <specific name="Key Skill"> Arcana </specific>
    <specific name="Component Cost"> 50 GP </specific>
    <specific name="Duration"> Until discharge </specific>
    <specific name="Level"> 4 </specific>
    <specific name="Time"> 10 minutes </specific>
    <specific name="Market Price"> 150 gp </specific>
    <specific name="Prerequisite" />
    <specific name="type"> Ritual </specific>
Thieves and adventurers who want to gain access to a building by way of a window sometimes employ this ritual, though more often than not they simply sacrifice a slab of glass in order to gain a form of concealment and some protection. A snowflake is engraved over the windowpane with a diamond-tipped tool before the glass is smashed. This operation is soundless thanks to the magic imbued into the pane from the very beginning; moreover, the shards remain in suspension around a single character designed during the ritual thereafter, forming an ever moving cloud that provides concealment just like a heavy falling snow would (for more details about Concealment consult the D&amp;D 4E PLAYER'S HANDBOOK). This screen of glass particles is not very discreet however, reflecting any light sources, thus it often attracts unwanted attention (increase the DC of any Stealth checks by 5 when any light is present).

The swirling cloud occupies a space around the recipient that is equivalent to a close burst 1. Anyone who tries to enter this space or remains inside the area is mercilessly buffeted by the cutting shards, suffering 1d4 damage each round, and is blinded (save ends). The cloud is soon used up in such a situation however, delivering damage only for a total of 5 rounds or less (this aspect depending upon the Arcana check); the cloud moreover loses its potency if flings as a blast thereafter (see below), dealing 1d4 damage less for each round where it has been previously worn out and losing special effects accordingly.

The cloud of broken glass can be hurled at anytime against foes in the form of a blast. The use of this power is a standard action that targets each creature in the blast. The attack uses the recipient's Intelligence against the target(s) Reflex. The area of effect of the blast and the amount of damage dealt are both determined by the Arcana check along with special effects if any.

&lt;table&gt;Arcana Check Result	Area of Effect	Damage	Special Effects
9 or lower	Blast 1	1d4	None
10-14	Blast 2	2d4	Hit: Target is pushed 1 square Miss: Half damage only
15-19	Blast 3	3d4	Hit: Target is pushed 1 square and is blinded (save ends) Miss: Half damage only
20-24	Blast 4	4d4	Hit: Target is pushed 2 squares and is blinded (save ends) Miss: Half damage only
25-29	Blast 5	5d4	Hit: Target is pushed 2 squares, knocked prone, and is blinded (save ends) Miss: Half damage only
30 or higher	Blast5	20	Hit: Target is unconscious Miss: Half damage only&lt;/table&gt;

</RulesElement>
