  <RulesElement name="The Spirit of the Letter" type="Ritual" internal-id="ID_TIV_RITUAL_MAGICAL_MEMORIES_100_6" source="Magical Memories from Beyond: Forgotten Rituals" revision-date="1/11/2011 3:22:33 PM">
    <Flavor> The ghostlike scrivener takes its place behind the desk and begins the translation of the huge volume written in Draconic there, the faithful transcription of every page appearing in Common in the second book. </Flavor>
    <specific name="Category"> Exploration </specific>
    <specific name="Key Skill"> Arcana or Religion </specific>
    <specific name="Component Cost"> 100 gp </specific>
    <specific name="Duration"> Special </specific>
    <specific name="Level"> 5 </specific>
    <specific name="Time"> 10 minutes </specific>
    <specific name="Market Price"> 250 gp </specific>
    <specific name="Prerequisite" />
    <specific name="type"> Ritual </specific>
This ritual brings into existence the spirit of a non-described scribe that is capable to read aloud a tome or transcript a text designed by you while simultaneously doing the translation of the work, being moreover able to switch from one language to another as required. The number of languages known by the phantasmal scribe thus conjured depends upon the Arcana or Religion check result, but the caster is the one who determines which languages the translator effectively knows (see the list below). Implements such as ink, quills, parchments, or blank books must be provided to the spirit, which can then reproduce faithfully any tome down to the minute details, including annotations in margin, drawings, illuminations and plans if any are present. The spirit can tirelessly copy or translate the entire content of a page in six minutes regardless the nature of the work therein, including rituals and spells. If a scribe has finished a specific job and that the duration of its service is not over yet it can be assigned a new task, else it simply remains still.

If the volume upon which the phantom scribe works ever contains a Secret Page or more (see this ritual in the D&amp;D 4E PLAYER'S HANDBOOK) the scrivener is entitled to a Perception check to notice the hidden passages, using the passive Perception of the ritual's performer in order to do so. You can order the scribe to specifically look for all the Secret Pages contained within the pages of a given book, but in that case half its' time is devoted to that task, which results in fewer pages transcribed. Moreover, the scrivener does the copy of the false pages and that of the real ones as well when it discovers a Secret Page, leaving the elucidation of such passages to the reader.

&lt;table&gt;Arcana or Religion Check Result	Number of Languages Known	Duration
9 or lower	Common plus another language	1 hour or 10 pages
10-14	Common plus two more languages	2 hours or 20 pages
15-19	Common plus three more languages	3 hours or 30 pages
20-24	Common plus four more languages	4 hours or 40 pages
25-29	Common plus five more languages	8 hours or 80 pages
30-34	Common plus six more languages	16 hours or 160 pages
35-39	Common plus seven more languages	1 day or 240 pages
40 or higher	All	1 week or 1,680 pages&lt;/table&gt;

Language in alphabetic order: Abyssal, Common, Deep Speech, Draconic, Dwarven, Elven, Giant, Goblin, Primordial, and Supernal.

</RulesElement>
