  <RulesElement name="Time Arrow" type="Ritual" internal-id="ID_TIV_RITUAL_MAGICAL_MEMORIES_100_7" source="Magical Memories from Beyond: Forgotten Rituals" revision-date="1/11/2011 3:22:33 PM">
    <Flavor> The Lady Ranger seized the ritually prepared arrow, knocked it, and fired down the empty corridor all in the blink of an eye. To her utmost astonishment, the missile stopped as soon as it left the bow, suspended in midair. "It works!" she said, genuinely taken aback. The wizard only smiled at her as he addressed the arrow. "Strike the first orc as soon as it appears." </Flavor>
    <specific name="Category"> Exploration </specific>
    <specific name="Key Skill"> Arcana </specific>
    <specific name="Component Cost"> 50 gp plus a focus worth 250 gp </specific>
    <specific name="Duration"> Until discharge </specific>
    <specific name="Level"> 3 </specific>
    <specific name="Time"> 1 hour </specific>
    <specific name="Market Price"> 200 gp </specific>
    <specific name="Prerequisite" />
    <specific name="type"> Ritual </specific>
This ritual empowers a single ranged weapon (any weapon that possesses a range qualify, regardless the name of the ritual) or a single projectile fired from a ranged weapon with the capability to remain in temporal stasis until a given condition has been fulfilled, a short command being formulated to set the moment of its release while the weapon is static. This order must be concise and expressed in less than 15 words else the ritual fails. If an event occurs before the instruction has been entirely worded, like the apparition of an unexpected enemy in front of the missile, the projectile remains fixed in place and can still be commanded as the situation required (a free action); once completed the instructions cannot be altered however.

The attack is conducted like a normal ranged attack and uses the attack roll of the character that has launched the missile. A character capable to fire more than once in a round, like a ranger using the Twin Strike exploit for example, or someone who has more than one round to get ready, can effectively release many missiles prepared with this ritual if enough are available; note that when a power is employed the ritual must abide to the letter of that power regarding the target(s) entry. Thus, a ranger attacking with the Twin Strike exploit can target either one or two creatures, but not so if she strikes with the Two-Fanged Strike exploit, the late one stipulating under target only one creature. Also, an elf that has rolled poorly when he has fired one of these special shots can resort to Elven Accuracy and make use of the second roll.

This ritual is sometimes used as trap, though the wording of the command must be explicit enough in that case; many characters who utilize the ritual as such often state something akin to "Strike anyone and anything but me who approaches this zone." If a projectile ever remains in stasis because the directive was too vague - or ironically, because someone arrives opposite the direction the missile points at - it can simply be plucked by anyone who can reach it and employed like a normal object; however the temporal stasis that holds the thing in the air doesn't prevent its deterioration, and a weapon that stays immobile for years can show significant traces of decay.

Focus: 
An hourglass filled with silver dust worth at least 250 gp.

</RulesElement>
