  <RulesElement name="Timeless Reflection" type="Ritual" internal-id="ID_TIV_RITUAL_MAGICAL_MEMORIES_100_8" source="Magical Memories from Beyond: Forgotten Rituals" revision-date="1/11/2011 3:22:33 PM">
    <Flavor> The lady's fingertips brushed against the oblong looking-glass at the same time that she asked "Show me exactly when my sister has been killed or murdered". The perfect, silvery surface blurred briefly, than the horrible scene that occurred more than a year ago in front of this very mirror repeated itself entirely. </Flavor>
    <specific name="Category"> Divination </specific>
    <specific name="Key Skill"> Arcana </specific>
    <specific name="Component Cost"> 25,000 gp plus a focus worth 10,000 gp </specific>
    <specific name="Duration"> Special </specific>
    <specific name="Level"> 25 </specific>
    <specific name="Time"> 1 hour </specific>
    <specific name="Market Price"> 125,000 gp </specific>
    <specific name="Prerequisite" />
    <specific name="type"> Ritual </specific>
This ritual allows you to witness first hand a specific event from the past that has obligatory taken place in front of a given reflective plane - a mirror, window, or any surface that generates a perceptible reflection - just like if you were tapping into some virtual memory the object had possessed. You can see and hear in the mirror's depths a conform re-enactment of what has transpired from the surface's point(s) of view. Thus, if the place was in total darkness, therefore no images are conveyed, although sounds might still be perceptible if there were any. If the surface wasn't clean at the time of the event than the play can be seen through a hazy veil, and so on. It is also possible that the action didn't take place exactly in front of the reflective surface but somewhere else in the whole picture the mirror has "memorized"; an observer can always move left or right while the performance unfolds and gains new perspectives regarding the area and the drama - many spectators acting in concert can even gain more information by occupying many positions at once.

The moment in time you want to observe must be worded as precisely as you can; if the description is not precise enough the ritual fails, though the components aren't expended in that case. Same holds true if the object hadn't seen the event about which you referred to.

This ritual doesn't provide the participants with darkvision, nor with any other special powers for that matter; anyone who witnesses the chain of events can use Perception checks to sort out details however.

Magical wards in place in the mirror's vicinity at the time of the event - like the Forbiddance ritual - are now completely irrelevant and cannot prevent this temporal intrusion.

Your Arcana check result determines how far in the past you can go back and for how long you can observe the episode that takes place at the designated moment in time you decided on. If the looking-glass from which you recall the experience is still occupying the same ground as it did at the time of the incident you gain a +5 modifier to your Arcana check.

&lt;table&gt;Arcana Check Result	Period Back in Time	Period of Time Showed
19 or lower	1 month	1 round
20-24	1 year	1 minute
25-29	1 decade	10 minutes
30-34	1 century	1 hour
35-39	1 millennium	10 hours
40 or higher	No limits	1 day&lt;/table&gt;

Focus: 
An hourglass filled with diamond dust worth at least 10,000 gp.
</RulesElement>
