  <RulesElement name="Wild Jester" type="Ritual" internal-id="ID_TIV_RITUAL_MAGICAL_MEMORIES_100_9" source="Magical Memories from Beyond: Forgotten Rituals" revision-date="1/11/2011 3:22:33 PM">
    <Flavor> The pair of guards looked sidelong at the motley she-harlequin coming their way, the lady hopping joyously and humming a merry tune all the while. "Seems we're going to enjoy this festival a little bit after all" said the first suggestively. The second only smiled, but his grin didn't hold for long as the fire nearby was snuffed all the sudden. Then, the lady-jester was upon him, pummeling him senseless with the thin metallic scepter she held firmly in her hand. </Flavor>
    <specific name="Category"> Creation </specific>
    <specific name="Key Skill"> Arcana </specific>
    <specific name="Component Cost"> 1,200 GP </specific>
    <specific name="Duration"> Permanent until destroyed </specific>
    <specific name="Level"> 12 </specific>
    <specific name="Time"> 8 hours </specific>
    <specific name="Market Price"> 6,000 gp </specific>
    <specific name="Prerequisite" />
    <specific name="type"> Ritual </specific>
Originally conceived as toys for many kings and emperors, these already sophisticated, fully-articulated mannequins were soon enhanced further and turned into superb automatons, endowed with intelligence, physical skills, combat capabilities, and simple magical abilities. In fact a wild jester is capable to cast only cantrips, these late ones being incorporated in its "mind" during the ritual, their total number being determined by the Arcana check. Possible cantrips include - but are not limited to - the following ones: Ghost Sound, Light, Mage Hand, and Prestidigitation.

The harlequin or jester suit, though not obligatory, often remains the trademark of these constructs along with various masks, which conceal their true nature. A wild jester is linked to its proprietor thanks to an identical set of scepters known as baubles or marottes, each individual obligatory holding one. The rods are deceptively fragile in appearance, but can effectively serve as weapons. If ever disarmed, a wild jester carries on the last order it has received to the best of its abilities. Taking away the proprietor's rod for more than 24 hours has the same effect, an individual requiring an entire day to attune itself to the construct if he ever wants to control it. A wild jester that is no longer directed becomes a free-thinking individual when more than an entire day has passed and can no longer be controlled in this fashion ever again.

&lt;table&gt;Arcana Check Result	Number of Wizard Cantrips The Wild Jester Knows
14 or lower	1
15-19	2
20-24	3
25-29	4
30 or higher	5&lt;/table&gt;

      <specific name="_DisplayPowers"> ID_TIV_COMPANION_0001 </specific>

Marotte: A marotte, or bauble, is a prop stick or sceptre with a carved head that is typically carried by a fool, harlequin, or jester. In this particular case it's a light mace made from the finest and most resilient steel, which is deceptively fragile-looking. The marotte can be used as an off-hand weapon.

